    <p><strong>Bakery display counter prices in India range from ₹20,000 for a simple ambient bread counter to ₹2.5 lakh or more for a premium refrigerated curved-glass pastry display.</strong> A good display counter is one of the most important investments in your bakery's retail operation — it's what customers see when they walk in, and it directly influences how much they buy. This guide covers all types available in India with honest pricing and expert buying advice.</p>

    <h2>Types of Bakery Display Counters in India</h2>

    <h3>1. Ambient (Non-Refrigerated) Bread & Pastry Display</h3>
    <p>Ambient display counters are used for products that don't need refrigeration — bread loaves, rusks, cookies, croissants, and most pastries. They keep products visible and fresh-looking without cooling. Glass panels protect from dust and customer handling while maintaining visibility.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Price range:</strong> ₹20,000 – ₹75,000</li>
      <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Bread bakeries, snack counters, ambient pastries</li>
      <li><strong>Sizes:</strong> 60cm, 90cm, 120cm, and 150cm widths are standard</li>
      <li><strong>Materials:</strong> SS frame with toughened glass panels. Some models with LED interior lighting</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2. Refrigerated Cake & Pastry Display Counter</h3>
    <p>Refrigerated display counters maintain 4–8°C to keep cream-filled cakes, chilled pastries, mousses, and other temperature-sensitive items fresh. These are the most important piece of display equipment for a cake shop or dessert-focused bakery.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Price range:</strong> ₹60,000 – ₹2,50,000</li>
      <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Cake shops, pastry bakeries, dessert counters</li>
      <li><strong>Types:</strong> Front-service (staff picks items from behind) or self-service (customers take items themselves)</li>
      <li><strong>Key feature:</strong> LED internal lighting dramatically improves product presentation</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Curved Glass Display Counter</h3>
    <p>Curved-glass display counters are the premium option — they create a more upscale presentation and are popular in hotel bakeries, five-star cake shops, and upmarket pastry boutiques. The curved glass gives maximum visibility from all angles.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Price range:</strong> ₹1,20,000 – ₹4,00,000</li>
      <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Upscale bakeries, hotel pastry shops, premium cake counters</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4. Island Display Counter</h3>
    <p>Free-standing island counters are placed in the centre of the retail floor, allowing customers to browse from all sides. Popular in supermarket bakery sections and large retail bakeries with high foot traffic.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Price range:</strong> ₹80,000 – ₹3,00,000</li>
      <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Large retail bakeries, supermarket sections</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5. Upright Glass-Door Display Fridge</h3>
    <p>Tall vertical display refrigerators with glass doors. More storage capacity than horizontal counters. Less suitable for upscale presentation but highly practical for high-volume operations. Also used for cold beverages in bakery cafés.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Price range:</strong> ₹35,000 – ₹1,50,000</li>
      <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Volume display, beverages, practical storage with visibility</li>
    </ul>

