    <h2>What to Look for in a Bakery Display Counter</h2>

    <h3>Temperature Uniformity (Refrigerated Models)</h3>
    <p>A refrigerated display counter must maintain consistent temperature throughout its interior — not just near the cooling unit. Poor-quality counters have warm spots, particularly at the top front, which can lead to product spoilage. Ask about temperature uniformity specifications.</p>

    <h3>LED Internal Lighting</h3>
    <p>LED lighting inside the display counter makes products look dramatically more appealing. It's not just aesthetics — well-lit products sell better. LED lights also generate less heat than fluorescent tubes, reducing the load on the refrigeration system.</p>

    <h3>Glass Quality</h3>
    <p>Display counters should use toughened (tempered) glass for safety. Curved glass should be low-iron (ultra-clear) glass for maximum transparency — regular glass has a greenish tint that makes food look less appealing.</p>

    <h3>Condensation Management</h3>
    <p>In India's humid climate, glass fogging and condensation on refrigerated display counters is a major issue. Look for counters with heated glass (an electric element in the glass that prevents condensation) or anti-fog glass treatment. A counter with foggy glass is essentially invisible — defeating the purpose of a display.</p>

    <h3>Dimensions and Layout</h3>
    <p>Standard counter height is 90–95 cm (comfortable for staff to reach across). Depth is typically 50–70 cm. For a retail bakery with a front counter, you'll usually need 120–240 cm of total counter length.</p>

    <h2>Top Bakery Display Counter Brands in India</h2>
    <p><strong>Imported brands:</strong> Criocabin (Italy), Arneg (Italy), Infrico (Spain) — premium quality, highest prices, best for upscale bakeries and hotels</p>
    <p><strong>Asian brands:</strong> Hoshizaki (Japan), Blue Star commercial line — good quality, mid-range pricing</p>
    <p><strong>Indian fabricators:</strong> Many quality fabricators in Delhi, Mumbai, and Bangalore make custom display counters. Quality varies widely. For a custom counter, always inspect the fabricator's previous work. Prices: ₹20,000 – ₹1,50,000 for custom-fabricated ambient and refrigerated counters</p>

