    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What is the price of a bakery display counter in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Bakery display counter prices in India range from ₹20,000 for a basic ambient bread display to ₹4 lakh or more for a premium refrigerated curved-glass pastry counter. For most small-to-medium bakeries, a good refrigerated counter 120 cm wide costs ₹90,000 – ₹1,50,000.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Do I need a refrigerated display counter for my bakery? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">If you sell cream-filled cakes, chilled pastries, mousses, eclairs, or any temperature-sensitive products, a refrigerated display counter is essential — both for product safety and FSSAI compliance. If you only sell ambient products (bread, cookies, rusks, dry pastries), an ambient counter is sufficient.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How wide should a bakery display counter be? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">A small café or bakery retail counter typically needs 120–180 cm of total display length. A medium bakery benefits from 180–300 cm. A large retail bakery may need 300–500 cm or more. Consider both the total length of products you want to display and the space available in your retail area.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can I get a custom display counter made in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Many stainless steel and glass fabricators in major Indian cities make custom display counters. Custom fabrication lets you get exact dimensions and specifications. For non-refrigerated ambient counters, local fabrication is very competitive (₹15,000 – ₹50,000). For refrigerated counters, it's harder to fabricate locally — better to buy from an established manufacturer or importer to ensure proper refrigeration performance.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What temperature should a bakery display counter maintain? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">For cream cakes and chilled pastries: 2–4°C. For general chilled baked goods: 4–8°C. For beverages and grab-and-go items: 4–8°C. FSSAI guidelines require that chilled ready-to-eat foods be maintained below 8°C at all times in display. Never use a refrigerated display for items that should be served ambient — the temperature can affect texture and appearance.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

